name: Attorney General Kathy Jennings
tweet: But it restores the authority that sentencing judges are meant to have in a criminal justice system that is predicated on evaluating facts and tailoring individual punishments to individual crimes, and it rejects the failed one size fits all system of the past.

tweet: HB 5 still allows judge to hand down consecutive sentences if they believe that doing so would serve justice, and it preserves mandatory consecutive sentences in the very most violent crimes.

name: Attorney General Kathy Jennings
tweet: Under HB 5, sentencing judges will have the discretion in most cases to impose multiple sentences concurrently, rather than consecutively. Previously, sentencing judges were bound by law to impose consecutive sentences in many cases.
